{
  "texts": [
    "In this work, we explored the effects of pruning on the jailbreaking resistance of large language models.",
    "By applying WANDA pruning at varying levels of sparsity to LLaMA-2-7B-Chat, Vicuna 1.3, and Mistral Instruct v0.2 models, we obtained an assortment of compressed models.",
    "We further curated a dataset of 225 malicious tasks and 2250 jailbreaking prompts, with which we evaluated our base and compressed models.",
    "Our results show that if the unpruned model is sufficiently safety trained, then safety improves at lower sparsities of pruning, but then a reversal in the trend when pruned more aggressively.",
    "This suggests the possibility of using a carefully selected amount of pruning to aid in the deployment of safe LLMs."
  ]
}